      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: A) 1</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Mandatory exploration is generally required for injuries in <strong>Zone 1</strong> of the retroperitoneum.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:658px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"4\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Zones of retroperitoneum</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Zones</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>1</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>2</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>3</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Location</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Central</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Lateral</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Pelvic</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>(retroperitoneal zone of the pelvis)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Structures involve</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ce68eab48a1692777181c719b4344e\">aorta</span> & its <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bdbac654081692777196f9aab116f0\">proximal</span> branches</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Inferior <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3ddf6d5ea71692777201b70c8b9715\">vena</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"67544ba6ef16927771835d4641cc8f\">cava</span> & its <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bdbac654081692777196f9aab116f0\">proximal</span> tributaries</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Distal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b9356afdba16927771979d068c6587\">renal</span> vessels</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Iliac vessels</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Management</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<p><strong>(Other options ruled out)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Exploration with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bdbac654081692777196f9aab116f0\">proximal</span> & <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5ff25303a01692777186731f6a4f5c\">distal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"526ede3fee169277720184378acc5e\">vascular</span> control</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Lateral <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"832849414c1692777188491f77bb5f\">hematoma</span> (renal in origin) - managed nonoperatively (angioembolization)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pulsatile <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"832849414c1692777188491f77bb5f\">hematoma</span> or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55b31d659b16927771958a15837b10\">penetrating</span> injury present - exploration.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pelvic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"832849414c1692777188491f77bb5f\">hematoma</span> is exceptionally difficult to control.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Usually, it should not be opened. It is managed by packing/angioembolisation.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Explored only if there is expanding or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a2af1612021692777196c7044ee75b\">pulsatile</span> or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55b31d659b16927771958a15837b10\">penetrating</span> injury present.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>",
