      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Option A. </strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Achalasia cardia: Heller's operation, also known as Heller myotomy, is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> procedure performed to treat <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b032d2af58169277718080a9060b14\">Achalasia</span> cardia. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b032d2af58169277718080a9060b14\">Achalasia</span> is a condition characterized by the inability of the lower <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"192677035a169277718780b4d6dbbb\">esophageal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1a73a42f071692777199a59120f494\">sphincter</span> (LES) to relax properly, leading to difficulty in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1788e0d4301692777199d457616bd4\">swallowing</span> and the accumulation of food in the esophagus. Heller's operation involves cutting the muscles of the lower <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"192677035a169277718780b4d6dbbb\">esophageal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1a73a42f071692777199a59120f494\">sphincter</span> to alleviate the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"39f44b27bf169277719416f29a74ee\">obstruction</span> and improve the passage of food into the stomach.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Incorrect Options:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Option B</strong>. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"988c19e3131692777183b6744d1920\">Carcinoma</span> esophagus: Heller's operation is not performed for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"988c19e3131692777183b6744d1920\">carcinoma</span> of the esophagus. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"988c19e3131692777183b6744d1920\">Carcinoma</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6a729a105a169277718788389dbeab\">esophagus</span> typically requires other treatment modalities such as surgery, chemotherapy, radiation therapy, or a combination of these approaches.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Option C</strong>. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"192677035a169277718780b4d6dbbb\">Esophageal</span> stricture: Heller's operation is not commonly performed for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"192677035a169277718780b4d6dbbb\">esophageal</span> strictures. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"192677035a169277718780b4d6dbbb\">Esophageal</span> strictures are often managed using other methods such as <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"35ca8c2d5f16927771879351e8f97e\">endoscopic</span> dilation, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cb33defbb316927771991b2ef81ec3\">stent</span> placement, or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> resection, depending on the underlying cause and severity of the stricture.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Option D</strong>. Hypertrophic pyloric stenosis: Heller's operation is not indicated for hypertrophic pyloric stenosis. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2cf4f27ae616927771895f410747ad\">Hypertrophic pyloric stenosis</span> is a condition that affects infants and causes narrowing of the pylorus, leading to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4a2cfb12bc1692777196456d7fb26b\">projectile vomiting</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"11a5eea407169277720251b8446fa7\">feeding</span> difficulties. The treatment for <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2cf4f27ae616927771895f410747ad\">hypertrophic pyloric stenosis</span> typically involves a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> procedure called pyloromyotomy, which involves making an <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2afbd932801692777190be690704b3\">incision</span> in the muscle of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8e56d9271316927771965c8ad6e48d\">pylorus</span> to relieve the obstruction.</p>",
